<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_kʼæsær" xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼæsær</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>порог</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>doorstep</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>tæxūdy nyr wæ kʼæsæræj k˳y bazarin æz dær</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>о, если бы и мне запеть с вашего порога</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Oh, if only I could also sing from your doorstep</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>110</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>kæj koj kænaj — kʼæsærmæ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (д. %ike koj kænaj —
                    kʼæsærmæ%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (Digor %ike koj kænaj —
                    kʼæsærmæ%i)</note></quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>кого упомянешь — на пороге</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>whom you mention — he is at your doorstep</q>
            </cit>
            <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (поговорка: „легок на помине“)</note>
            <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (saying: “to talk of the devil (and he is sure to
                appear)”)</note>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 211</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>92</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>tæxūdy nyr wæ kʼæsæræj k˳y bazarin æz dær</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>о, если бы и мне запеть с вашего порога</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Oh, if only I could also sing from your doorstep</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>110</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>kæj koj kænaj — kʼæsærmæ<note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (д. %ike koj kænaj —
                    kʼæsærmæ%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (Digor %ike koj kænaj —
                    kʼæsærmæ%i)</note></quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>кого упомянешь — на пороге</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>whom you mention — he is at your doorstep</q>
            </cit>
            <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (поговорка: „легок на помине“)</note>
            <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (saying: “to talk of the devil (and he is sure to
                appear)”)</note>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 211</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>92</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Вряд ли производное от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæs"/> ‘хижина’:
        формант %i-ær%i не известен. Более вероятной кажется связь с <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
                ><lang/><w>kʼarseli</w><gloss><q>передняя</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Беридзе"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>), ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
            ><lang/><w>k’arse</w><gloss><q>порог</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ka-x-rach"><w/><gloss><q>косяк</q></gloss></mentioned>, („%izgurbli da
        cʼqirtli%i“: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Саба"/><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>). Звуковое
        развитие: %ik’arseli%i → %i*kʼælsær%i → %ikʼæsær%i, как %ič’arxala%i → %i*cælxæra%i → <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_cæxæra"/> ‘свекла’.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It is hardly a derivative from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæs"/> ‘hut’:
        a formant %i-ær%i is unknown. The more probable relation is with <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
            ><lang/><w>kʼarseli</w><gloss><q>entrance-room</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Беридзе"/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>), cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
            ><lang/><w>k’arse</w><gloss><q>doorstep</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ka-x-rach"><w/><gloss><q>jamb</q></gloss></mentioned>, („%izgurbli da
        cʼqirtli%i“: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Саба"/><biblScope>163</biblScope></bibl>). The sound
        evolution: %ik’arseli%i → %i*kʼælsær%i → %ikʼæsær%i, as in %ič’arxala%i → %i*cælxæra%i →
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæxæra"/> ‘beetroot’.</etym>
    <note type="internal">ужасный сорс</note>
</entry>
